This atelier actually has quite a few students
\>What \c[4]Skill Plugins\c[0] would you like to learn about?\<

<WordWrap>The \c[4]Skill Core\c[0] plugin enables you to modify the core aspects of skills such as the cost and effects. With this plugin, \HP costs are also implemented, too. This plugin sets up the basic framework for many extension plugins.
<WordWrap>This plugin enables you to set a limited amount of times certain skills (or all skills) can be used per battle or ever.
<WordWrap>This adds a different type of skill currency and balance mechanic in limiting the amount of times a skill can be used without directly having to alter \MP, \TP, or the like.
<WordWrap>This plugin requires the \c[4]Skill Core\c[0] plugin and enables a \c[4]Party Limit Gauge\c[0] for both the player party and the enemy party.
<WordWrap>These gauges will fill up or decrease depending on what actions take place.
<WordWrap>The amounts they raise can be adjusted within the plugin's parameters to your liking.
<WordWrap>Once a party has enough of the \c[4]Party Limit Gauge\c[0], members from that party can use it as a skill resource to unleash powerful actions in battle!
<WordWrap>\c[4]Skill Cooldowns\c[0] is an extension plugin for the \c[4]Skill Core\c[0].

<WordWrap>This plugin enables you to give your skills cooldowns, a game mechanic which prevents skills from being repeatedly used requiring the player to wait a few turns in order for the skill to become available for use again.
<WordWrap>Now you can set costs for skills using items. The item costs will appear next to the other skill costs displaying the icons of the items needed and the amount of the items to be used.
<WordWrap>Item costs using this plugin can be altered by set and percentile amounts in addition to being replaced altogether by a substitute item.
<WordWrap>\c[4]Instant Cast\c[0] allows for skills and items to be instantly used after being selected without using up the users turn!
<WordWrap>This plugin enables your games actors to learn skills from the skill menu.
<WordWrap>This can be done via either gold, items, or \c[4]Job Points\c[0].
<WordWrap>It provides the player an alternate way of acquiring skills aside from leveling up.
<WordWrap>\c[4]Item Synthesis\c[0] is now a pretty common aspect of most RPG's where the player can craft their own items after acquiring recipes.
<WordWrap>This plugin enables your players to be able to do that after acquiring the said recipes.
<WordWrap>Recipes can come in the form of items, weapons, and/or armors and transcribed in them are what items, weapons, and/or armors they can make.
<WordWrap>These items can be made from the main menu and/or synthesis locations!
